dbackModal_main_3610186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104smq1665702871520.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/smq1665702871520.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/smq1665702871520.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"smq1665702871520\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Changing the Widget Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Changing the widget type creates a (local) definition of a field that deviates from the application model default.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"smq1665702871520__p_d25544e1_d25545e1_d25546e1\">Deviations of this sort do not cause errors, because at run time Uniface ignores any properties that the GUI (or widget type) does not recognize. Uniface uses the defaults of the project GUI for all undefined properties.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"smq1665702871520__li_d12647e1_d12648e1_d12649e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Ensure that the values of all common widget properties are consistent for all widget\n               types. You can then change widget types irrespective of style guidelines. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"smq1665702871520__p_d25547e1_d25548e1_d25549e1\">For example, if <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Font</span>\n               specifies a suitable font for a list box field, you should be able to change the\n               widget type of that field to another type that also recognizes the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Font</span> property, such as a radio group, without needing to\n               adjust the font.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"smq1665702871520__li_d12650e1_d12651e1_d12652e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Change the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Type</span> property for the entity or field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"smq1665702871520__p_d25550e1_d25551e1_d25552e1\">If you change a widget's type after explicitly\n               defining common properties for that widget, either in the application model or in the\n               widget properties, the common properties are also defined for the new widget\n               type.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"smq1665702871520__p_d25553e1_d25554e1_d25555e1\">If you change a widget that has unique properties (for example, changing a meter to a progress bar) the properties of the old widget are still available in the More Properties dialog box.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjk1665702557273.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widgets</a><p>In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3610186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3610186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Changing the Widget Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Changing the Widget Type Changing the widget type creates a (local) definition of a field that deviates from the application model default. Deviations of this sort do not cause errors, because at run time Uniface ignores any properties that the GUI (or widget type) does not recognize. Uniface uses the defaults of the project GUI for all undefined properties. Ensure that the values of all common widget properties are consistent for all widget types. You can then change widget types irrespective of style guidelines. For example, if Font specifies a suitable font for a list box field, you should be able to change the widget type of that field to another type that also recognizes the Font property, such as a radio group, without needing to adjust the font. Change the Widget Type property for the entity or field. If you change a widget's type after explicitly defining common properties for that widget, either in the application model or in the widget properties, the common properties are also defined for the new widget type. If you change a widget that has unique properties (for example, changing a meter to a progress bar) the properties of the old widget are still available in the More Properties dialog box. Related Links Widgets In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}